The key idea: `session_success_rate` is a raw crash metric — 0.0 means the session failed (build/test break, API error, timeout). But it can't tell the difference between a crashed session and a clean no-op session that found nothing to fix. `session_productivity_rate` is the companion — it tracks sessions that landed verified code changes, so a clean no-op session lowers productivity without flagging it as a crash.

